column11:
  Motivated by the recent work of Hirschhorn on vanishing coefficients of the
arithmetic progressions in certain $q$-series expansions, we study some
variants of these $q$-series and prove some comparable results. For instance,
let \begin{align*}
(-q,-q^{4};q^{5})_{\infty}^{2}(q^{4},q^{6};q^{10})_{\infty}=\sum_{n=0}^{\infty}a_{1}(n)q^{n},
\end{align*} then \begin{align*} a_{1}(5n+3)=0. \end{align*}
